    dc:date "2015" ;
    dc:title "Redescriptions of three species of freshwater crabs from the Democratic Republic of Congo, Central Africa (Brachyura: Potamoidea: Potamonautidae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.231931>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.231932>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.231933>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.231934> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.231931>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Potamonautes congoensis (Rathbun, 1921). Holotype, adult male, CW 44 mm, from the Nepoko River near Kisangani, D. R. Congo (AMNH 3354). A, carapace, frontal view; B, dorsal view; C, anterior thoracic sternum; D, right cheliped, frontal view; E, left cheliped, frontal view; F, carpus and merus of right cheliped, dorsal view; G, carpus and merus of right cheliped, ventral view; H, pereiopod 3; I, pleon (abdomen); J, third maxilliped, frontal view. Scale bar: 14.2 mm (A – I), 3.5 mm (J)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/231931/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.231932>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Potamonautes congoensis (Rathbun, 1921). Holotype, adult male, CW 44 mm, from the Nepoko River near Kisangani, D. R. Congo (AMNH 3354). A, G 1 ventral view; B, G 1 dorsal view; C, superior view of terminal article; D, G 2 ventral view; E, mandible frontal view; F, mandibular palp superior view. Scale bar: 4.5 mm (A – D), 2.5 mm (E – F)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/231932/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.231933>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Potamonautes congoensis (Rathbun, 1921). Holotype, adult male, CW 44 mm, from the Congo River at Kisangani, D. R. Congo (AMNH 3353). Whole animal A, dorsal view; B, ventral view. Scale bar: 20 mm (A – B)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/231933/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.231934>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12. Map of the D. R. Congo in Central Africa showing the known localities of P. congoensis (black circles, not shown to scale). See text for exact locality coordinates." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/231934/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

